    <td id="_ctl0__ctl4_ContentPane" colspan="2" valign="TOP" align="left"><!-- Start_Module_523 --><div id="_ctl0__ctl4_ModuleContent">
	
<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0 summary="Design Table">
  <TR vAlign=top>
    <TD id="_ctl0__ctl4__ctl0_HtmlHolder" class="Normal"><DIV class=row id=masthead>
<H3 id=siteName><FONT color=#000080 size=3><B>Priest&nbsp;Heroic Opportunity Tutorial</B></FONT></H3>
<H3><FONT color=#000080><STRONG>Heroic opportunity skills:</STRONG></FONT></H3>
<DIV id=content>
<DIV><BR>
<P class=feature>Almost every skill or spell that you get can be used to advance a heroic opportunity. If you right click on a skill or spell icon a list will come up. Choose examine from the menu and you will see a description of the skill or spell. You will also see a&nbsp;gold icon showing you what heroic opportunity icon it is associated with. For priests, there are three that we will be focusing on. We will also be focusing on your heroic opportunities that you can complete by yourself. These we call solo heroic opportunities. </P><BR>
<P class=feature>For this tutorial, we will assume that you have reached level 5. Level 5 is when you will get your heroic opportunity skill named Divine Providence. This skill has no casting time, it takes no mana to cast, and has a 10 second reuse timer. </P><BR>
<P class=feature><FONT color=#000080><STRONG>Identifying icons:</STRONG></FONT></P><BR>
<P class=feature>All&nbsp;priest heroic opportunity skills are colored gold. Scouts are green, mages are red, and fighters are blue. There are six icons for each archetype. The icons for&nbsp;priests are:&nbsp;Hammer, Eye, Chalice, Druidic Stones, Moon and Holy Symbol.&nbsp;</P><SPAN class="style3 feature"><FONT color=#000080><STRONG>Starting your first heroic opportunity (The Starter Chain):</STRONG></FONT> </SPAN><BR>
<P class=feature>To begin your heroic opportunity use a combat skill, spell, or use auto attack to begin combat with a creature. Next, press your&nbsp;Divine Providence&nbsp;hotkey that should be located in your bar at the bottom of your screen. You will see what is called a starter chain appear in the lower right hand corner of your screen with a&nbsp;Druidic Stones&nbsp;icon in the center. There are several other icons circling the&nbsp;Druidic Stones. The only&nbsp;gold&nbsp;icon is the hammer, so you will need to use a skill that has a&nbsp;hammer icon.&nbsp;Smite&nbsp;is the first skill that you will recieve that has a&nbsp;hammer icon associated with it. So, while targeting the creature, press your&nbsp;Smite skill. You will notice that the picture in the lower right hand corner has changed. It is now displaying what heroic opportunity you have started.<BR></P>
<H3><B><FONT color=#000080>Ordered and unordered heroic opportunities:</FONT></B></H3><BR>
<P class=feature><SPAN class="feature style3"><IMG style="WIDTH: 41px; HEIGHT: 45px" height=45 alt="" hspace=0 src="/Portals/6/unordered.gif" width=41 align=middle border=0><IMG style="WIDTH: 42px; HEIGHT: 45px" height=51 alt="" hspace=0 src="/Portals/6/ordered.gif" width=43 align=middle border=0>&nbsp;</SPAN>Heroic opportunities are either ordered or unordered. If a HO is ordered, then the icons in the HO wheel must be done in the order that they are shown. If it is unordered, then it does not matter when you use your skill or spell. There are also three colors that the two icons can display. Yellow is for a heroic opportunity that is currently inprogress. Green is for a completed HO. And red is for a failed HO. This final color can display if you let the timer run out before making the next step in the HO. The timer is displayed as a blue circle around the HO. <SPAN class=style17>Note: </SPAN>In the examples on the left, the first icon is unordered and the second is ordered. </P><BR>
<H3 class="feature style3"><FONT color=#000080><IMG style="WIDTH: 42px; HEIGHT: 42px" height=42 alt="" hspace=0 src="/Portals/6/GreenPenny.gif" width=42 align=middle border=0>&nbsp; Heroic opportunity possibilities and "flipping the wheel":</FONT></H3>
<P class=feature>Each starter chain can bring up three possible heroic opportunities. A common, uncommon, and a rare. For the&nbsp;priest solo HO, they are:&nbsp;Divine Judgement, Inspiring Piety, and Blessings of Faith.&nbsp;If you have a&nbsp;scout in your group they can use an ability with the coin icon associated with it. This will &#8220;flip&#8221; the HO and&nbsp;you will get another chance at getting one of the other two heroic opportunities.&nbsp;This can be extremely usefull to get that direct damage out rather then a combat buff. This skill works on all HO's, not just your solo.<BR></P>
<H3 class="feature style3"><FONT color=#000080>Completing the heroic opportunity:</FONT></H3><BR>
<P class=feature>Now that you have the heroic opportunity wheel up, you need to look at the blinking icons in the wheel. For the&nbsp;priest solo heroic opportunities it can be one of two icons, either a hammer or a chalice icon. If it is a hammer icon, press your Smite to complete the heroic opportunity. If it is the chalice, then you need to use Minor Healing to complete the heroic opportunity</P></DIV></DIV></DIV> </TD>
	</TR></TABLE>
<!-- End_Module_523 -->
</div></td>

  </tr>
</table>


</td>

    
